Interface Group<T>

public interface Group<T> extends Iterable<T>

Group

The Group interface represents a collection of objects, typically organized as a tuple or a pair. It serves as a generic structure that can hold multiple objects together, allowing for logical grouping and manipulation of related data elements.

Implementations of this interface define how the group behaves and interacts with its constituent objects. It provides a foundation for creating and managing various types of groups that may have specific semantics and operations.

  • Method Details

    • createGroup

      @Nonnull static <A> Group<A> createGroup(@Nonnull List<A> list)
      Creates a Group instance from a given list of elements.

      This static method creates a Group instance based on the size of the input list. If the list contains exactly 2 elements, a Pair instance is returned. If the list contains exactly 3 elements, a Tuple instance is returned. For other list sizes, an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.

      Type Parameters:
      A - The type of elements in the list.
      Parameters:
      list - The list of elements.
      Returns:
      A Group instance representing the input list.
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - If the list size is not supported.
